        <mxCell id="fUe3NVcBme_qR7799I4q-139" parent="fUe3NVcBme_qR7799I4q-91" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;fontSize=13;" value="&lt;font&gt;- Note that in the current version, the energy deposition mode only counts energy lost by the primary. However, secondaries generated by this energy loss will still be tracked by the simulation and, should they undergo energy deposition events, the energy loss there will too. This effectively means that a portion of the energy lost by the primary is double counted. A fix exists but has not been pulled into main yet.&lt;/font&gt;" vertex="1">
